The history teacher is assessing the effectiveness of an education app using a mathematical model. The teacher modeled the effectiveness, E, of the app as a function of the time, t (in hours), a student spends on the app. The model is given by the function:

E(t) = \frac{500t}{100 + t}

Assume that the time a student spends on the app is a random variable, T, that has a probability density function given by:

f(t) = \begin{cases}
\frac{3(20 - t)}{200} & \text{for } 0 \leq t \leq 20 \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}

Find the expected value of the effectiveness, E(T), of the app.
